dplyr::summarise()
Another approach involved the use of dplyr‚Äôs summarise() along with across(), everything(), and an anonymous function. This approach was meant only to count the amount of missing values within each column.

starwars |&gt;
  summarise(across(everything(), \(x) sum(is.na(x))))

